# Pre-commit and pre-push checks

Before **every commit** and **every push**, run the full check suite from the repo root. **Do not commit or push** if any step fails.

## Required sequence (Bun)

Run in order; stop on first failure, fix, then re-run from the top:

```bash
bun run format
bun run typecheck
bun run lint
bun run test
```

| Step | Command | Purpose |
| ---- | ------- | ------- |
| Format | `bun run format` | Prettier; stage any formatting changes before commit |
| Typecheck | `bun run typecheck` | `tsc --build` across project references |
| Lint | `bun run lint` | ESLint (strict TypeScript rules) |
| Test | `bun run test` | Vitest (`**/*.spec.ts`) |

## Gate rules

- **No commit** while any check is failing.
- **No push** while any check is failing — even if a commit already exists locally, fix failures first or revert; do not publish broken state to the remote.
- After `format` modifies files, include those changes in the same commit.
- Re-run the **full** sequence after fixes (not only the step that failed).

## When to run

- Before `git commit`
- Before `git push` (including when the user asks to commit-and-push)
- After significant code changes, before handing off work

## On failure

1. Stop immediately.
2. Read and fix the reported errors.
3. Re-run all four commands from the beginning.
4. Only then commit or push.
